An aircraft is allowed to change frequency when so advised by the appropriate aeronautical station. Under which other condition(s) is the aircraft allowed to change the frequency?&nbsp;
1. Without prior notification to the aeronautical station, to get the necessary information to land at the planned destination on the ATIS frequency&nbsp;
2. After notifying the aeronautical station that a change of frequency is needed&nbsp;
3. In case of distress
